MENSURATION FORMULAE (2D shapes)
SQUARE:
s = length of a side
Perimeter = 4s
Area = s2
RECTANGLE:
l = length
w = width or breadth
Perimeter = 2(l + w)
Area = l w
TRIANGLE:
b = base, h = height
Perimeter = a + b + c
s = Semi-Perimeter =
Area =
b h =
PARALLELOGRAM:
b = base, h = height, a = side
Perimeter = 2(a + b)
Area = b h
RHOMBUS:
s = side
d1, d2 = diagonals
Perimeter = 4s
Area =
d1 d2
EQUILATERAL TRIANGLE:
a = side
Height =
a
Perimeter = 3a
Area =
a2
CIRCLE:
r = radius
d = diameter
Diameter = 2r
Perimeter = 2r
Area = r2
SECTOR:
r = radius,
s = arc length
= sector angle in degrees
Length of arc =
x 2r
Area of sector =
x r2
RING or ANNULUS:
r = inner radius
R = outer radius
Width = R r
Area = (R2 r2)
